Anonymous Sun 05 Nov 2023 15:14:27 No.60887399 Report
Quoted By: >>60887575
>>60887279
Not him, but:

On the one hand, you aren't wrong. There aren't a lot of coherent stories you could tell that don't include some element that someone else hasn't used. When humans tell stories we use certain conventions.

At the same time, and I don't want to come off as an asshole here, but a lot of these ideas, like isekai, are currently the flavor of the week and using them in Current Year can seem derivative at best. Even "deconstructions" have already been done.

I don't know if anyone's done a "reconstruction" version with regression time travel, though. "Reconstruction" is where you look at all the cynical "deconstructions" and, while acknowledging them, tell a story that uses the idea and shows how awesome it can be. It's like what "Super Robot Wars" did for the giant mecha genre. This requires a protagonist who is heroic in the conventional ways, though. "Reconstruction" doesn't work with wimps.
